Template: lite-nas/profile-transform-note
Type: note
Description: LiteNAS applies a managed host profile
 LiteNAS is not just an application package. It transforms this machine toward
 a LiteNAS-managed host profile with secure defaults, managed services, and
 controlled configuration.
 .
 Today the profile is still small, but it is intended to grow to cover more
 host hardening, validation, and platform services over time.

Template: lite-nas/replace-nats-config
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Replace the local NATS configuration with the LiteNAS configuration?
 LiteNAS expects NATS Server to use the configuration shipped with this package.
 Selecting Yes installs the LiteNAS NATS configuration into /etc/nats-server*
 and restarts nats-server.
 .
 Selecting No keeps the current NATS configuration unchanged. In that case you
 must configure NATS manually so LiteNAS services can work correctly.

Template: lite-nas/manual-nats-config-note
Type: note
Description: Manual NATS configuration will be required
 The existing NATS configuration will be kept.
 You must configure NATS manually for LiteNAS before LiteNAS services can
 communicate successfully.
